WEBVTT

00:01.488 --> 00:02.487
I found Lyman here

00:02.523 --> 00:04.124
snooping through
your black laptop.

00:04.135 --> 00:05.933
I didn't push him,
but I didn't help him.

00:05.968 --> 00:07.401
You are the only person
in my life

00:07.436 --> 00:08.836
that doesn't
keep secrets from me,

00:08.871 --> 00:10.004
and I owe you the same.

00:10.039 --> 00:11.405
Tony: I just
saw your wedding ring.

00:11.440 --> 00:14.508
The ring is not exactly
what it looks like.

00:14.543 --> 00:16.510
She's going after my friends
to do it...

00:16.545 --> 00:17.845
First with Ben, and now...

00:17.880 --> 00:20.147
This is a far cry from
the Margaux I knew last year.

00:20.182 --> 00:23.117
She's angry that we were forced
to lie about Daniel's death.

00:23.152 --> 00:24.885
The Daniel Grayson
Research Wing.

00:24.920 --> 00:26.487
The board is still struggling
with the idea

00:26.522 --> 00:27.821
of naming it after Daniel.

00:27.857 --> 00:30.190
I think it's time
we took that step to end this

00:30.226 --> 00:31.191
before <i>she</i> does.

00:31.227 --> 00:33.427
We can clear Daniel's name
together.

00:33.462 --> 00:34.662
The only way to end this

00:34.697 --> 00:36.664
is by you telling the world
the truth.

00:36.699 --> 00:38.132
[ Tires screech ]

00:38.167 --> 00:39.033
[ Gasps ]

00:39.068 --> 00:40.467
Margaux:
The baby... He's gone.

00:40.503 --> 00:41.969
Why was Emily with you?

00:42.004 --> 00:43.771
She pushed me.

00:45.000 --> 00:51.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:57.753 --> 01:00.320
[ Sighs ]

01:00.356 --> 01:02.089
Please have these returned

01:02.124 --> 01:04.458
and make sure
no other items are delivered.

01:04.492 --> 01:05.492
Right away.

01:05.528 --> 01:06.994
And Ms. LeMarchal's
daily news briefings

01:07.029 --> 01:09.196
are in the kitchen,
if she's up to it.

01:09.231 --> 01:10.927
Thank you.

01:10.951 --> 01:12.583
Margaux:
The clothes were beautiful.

01:12.618 --> 01:13.717
You're up.

01:13.752 --> 01:16.387
I'll send Brigitte out
for some breakfast for you.

01:16.405 --> 01:18.507
I can't eat.

01:18.527 --> 01:20.894
At what time is the
groundbreaking gala tomorrow?

01:22.497 --> 01:23.630
Darling.

01:23.665 --> 01:25.232
[ Smooches ]

01:25.267 --> 01:26.499
You don't have to attend.

01:28.003 --> 01:30.937
All we wanted
was to redeem Daniel's name.

01:30.973 --> 01:33.195
The hospital wing
is the closest we've come,

01:33.211 --> 01:37.313
and I need to see
something good after...

01:40.247 --> 01:44.216
How can I miss someone
I have never met?

01:45.683 --> 01:47.388
You're a mother,

01:47.423 --> 01:50.758
and Emily should be behind bars
for taking that away from you.

01:50.793 --> 01:53.794
Pushing you in front of that car
was attempted murder.

01:53.830 --> 01:56.464
And I intend to share that
with the prosecutor's office.

01:56.499 --> 01:59.200
No, Victoria, I...

02:02.205 --> 02:04.137
Let's focus on our family.

02:04.160 --> 02:05.606
No prosecutors.

02:05.642 --> 02:07.775
Too much blood has been shed.

02:07.810 --> 02:09.776
None of it is on your hands.

02:09.812 --> 02:11.812
If only that were true.

02:14.651 --> 02:18.831
I was so desperate
to expose Emily's secrets.

02:18.843 --> 02:21.522
I had Lyman Ellis
steal what he could

02:21.557 --> 02:23.446
off of Nolan's hard drive.

02:23.469 --> 02:25.841
Before he could deliver it...

02:25.865 --> 02:27.795
He was found dead...

02:27.830 --> 02:29.940
On my devil's errand.

02:29.963 --> 02:33.367
I should have listened to you
weeks ago and ended my revenge.

02:37.619 --> 02:39.521
Get some rest.

02:39.545 --> 02:40.641
Yeah.

02:57.994 --> 03:00.027
Paper delivery.

03:00.063 --> 03:02.130
Three days in a row.

03:02.153 --> 03:04.065
You don't have to
keep checking in on me.

03:04.100 --> 03:06.408
[ Chuckles ]
Am I that obvious?

03:06.431 --> 03:07.835
Well, I already
poured you a cup of coffee,

03:07.870 --> 03:09.737
so, yeah,
I'd say pretty obvious.

03:12.408 --> 03:15.046
[ Sighs ]
You doing okay today?

03:15.069 --> 03:18.561
Still wish that I could
reach out to Margaux.

03:19.416 --> 03:21.642
But I don't...
I don't even know what I would say.

03:21.677 --> 03:24.177
At least the groundbreaking
for Daniel's wing is tomorrow,

03:24.213 --> 03:26.380
so hopefully that will bring her
a little solace.

03:26.415 --> 03:28.882
Well, it's <i>you</i> that I'm
worried about at the moment.

03:29.984 --> 03:31.887
I'm trying
to keep my mind off it.

03:31.898 --> 03:33.034
Really? How?

03:33.070 --> 03:34.769
[ Footsteps approach ]

03:36.106 --> 03:37.139
Hey.

03:37.174 --> 03:38.538
Mr. Clarke.
Good morning.

03:38.555 --> 03:41.857
Sorry, the, uh,
alarm didn't go off.

03:41.892 --> 03:42.991
Job interview?

03:43.026 --> 03:45.227
Ben made detective.

03:45.262 --> 03:46.633
Yeah,
first day driving the Crown Vic.

03:46.645 --> 03:48.930
Oh. Well,
congratulations are in order.

03:48.966 --> 03:49.790
Thanks.

03:49.813 --> 03:51.692
All right,
I'm gonna take my coffee to go.

03:51.715 --> 03:55.370
I'm repairing the rigging today.
It's an all-day job.

03:55.406 --> 03:56.671
Same time tomorrow?

04:00.353 --> 04:01.810
You look great.

04:01.846 --> 04:03.423
You have time
for some breakfast?

04:03.447 --> 04:05.147
You know,
I should probably get going, too.

04:05.182 --> 04:08.017
Before I forget...
My brother just texted me,

04:08.052 --> 04:09.651
and he's coming in
for this promotion party

04:09.687 --> 04:11.220
the guys are throwing me
tomorrow.

04:11.255 --> 04:13.611
And maybe to meet this hot girl
that I've been seeing.

04:13.623 --> 04:15.255
Oh, really?
Who's the girl?

04:15.278 --> 04:16.225
You don't know her.

04:16.260 --> 04:17.026
[ Chuckles ]

04:18.362 --> 04:20.107
I'll see you later.

04:25.703 --> 04:27.998
Louise:
Where is the cinnamon?

04:28.022 --> 04:31.340
I can't make Nanny Hettie's
French toast without cinnamon.

04:31.375 --> 04:32.174
[ Sighs ]

04:32.209 --> 04:32.975
Louise?

04:33.010 --> 04:35.351
Oh. I came back early.

04:35.374 --> 04:37.112
You have not seen family drama

04:37.148 --> 04:38.814
until you've
been to an Ellis funeral.

04:38.849 --> 04:39.815
It was horrible.

04:39.850 --> 04:42.194
I ate my weight in grits
in three days.

04:42.218 --> 04:45.488
Oh, see, I knew it.
I should have gone with you.

04:45.511 --> 04:49.369
Seeing Lyman in that coffin just
gutted me.

04:49.392 --> 04:50.793
And hearing Mama in front of

04:50.828 --> 04:52.795
all the rest of those
liars and cheats

04:52.830 --> 04:56.375
delivering a eulogy worthy
of Margaret Mitchell just...

04:56.398 --> 04:58.734
[ Sighs ]

04:58.769 --> 05:00.302
It just made me ill.

05:00.337 --> 05:02.805
[ Sighs ]

05:02.840 --> 05:05.808
The only lie I told myself was
that I could handle it alone.

05:06.682 --> 05:08.577
Well, you're...
You're home now.

05:09.324 --> 05:10.308
It's okay.

05:10.331 --> 05:11.681
What can I get you?

05:12.665 --> 05:14.750
- Well, two things.
- Mm-hmm.

05:14.785 --> 05:17.052
First, I really need
one of our wonder twin nights.

05:17.088 --> 05:18.353
[ Chuckles ]
They're so much better

05:18.389 --> 05:20.089
than three Xanax
and a glass of rosÃ©.

05:20.124 --> 05:22.958
Well, that is high praise.
What else?

05:25.783 --> 05:28.155
I want a baby.

05:28.178 --> 05:30.507
We could adopt one.

05:30.530 --> 05:31.763
[ Chuckles ]

05:32.797 --> 05:34.803
Wow.
[ Chuckles ]

05:34.839 --> 05:36.805
Well, we say we're like family,

05:36.841 --> 05:38.674
so why don't we just <i>be</i> one?

05:38.709 --> 05:42.377
We can raise a great kid in an open,
honest marriage

05:42.413 --> 05:46.181
and make up for the mistakes
our parents made with us.

05:46.217 --> 05:48.559
What do you think?

05:48.582 --> 05:50.519
I'm...

05:50.554 --> 05:51.920
I'm just...

05:51.956 --> 05:55.791
Still trying to decide
what we should do <i>tonight</i>, so...

05:57.795 --> 05:58.794
I know.

05:59.930 --> 06:02.837
I know. I...
It's too much too soon.

06:02.861 --> 06:04.299
I get it.

06:05.479 --> 06:07.836
Will you at least think about it?
Please?

06:07.872 --> 06:09.371
Mm-hmm.

06:11.483 --> 06:14.543
Alexander: I think you all understand
the gravity of this matter.

06:14.578 --> 06:15.878
Victoria:
Well, I've seen these.

06:15.913 --> 06:17.846
And they should have no bearing
on tomorrow's gala.

06:17.882 --> 06:19.181
The board's decision

06:19.216 --> 06:21.049
to name the new research wing
in your son's honor

06:21.085 --> 06:24.153
was predicated on our ability
to manage the publicity.

06:24.188 --> 06:25.587
Victoria: Well, silly me.

06:25.623 --> 06:28.820
And I thought it was predicated
on my $40 million donation.

06:28.844 --> 06:31.493
Women's groups say
we're rewarding a violent man.

06:31.529 --> 06:33.629
High-profile researchers
are pulling out.

06:33.664 --> 06:35.330
The board had no choice.

06:35.366 --> 06:37.799
There won't be
a Daniel Grayson Research Wing

06:37.835 --> 06:39.801
at this hospital.

06:39.837 --> 06:42.771
I have the full support
of LeMarchal Media behind me,

06:42.806 --> 06:46.002
and I can rebut this trash
in two hours,

06:46.025 --> 06:48.977
since I believe that the events
surrounding my son's death

06:49.013 --> 06:51.013
have been highly exaggerated.

06:52.383 --> 06:56.218
The board isn't comfortable with
this victim-shaming, Victoria.

06:56.253 --> 06:57.853
I'm no victim.

06:57.888 --> 07:01.690
I voted in support of the wing
because I have forgiven Daniel.

07:01.725 --> 07:05.160
He shouldn't be judged for
the last 15 minutes of his life.

07:05.196 --> 07:06.395
I move to reconsider.

07:06.430 --> 07:08.897
You've been gracious enough,
Ms. Thorne,

07:08.933 --> 07:11.266
but I'm afraid
this matter's settled.

07:13.437 --> 07:14.503
Victoria:
You realize this means

07:14.538 --> 07:16.980
I'll have to rescind my donation,
Alexander.

07:16.992 --> 07:18.340
In light of
the board's new stance,

07:18.375 --> 07:20.609
we've found other funding.

07:22.112 --> 07:24.179
So the groundbreaking
is still tomorrow.

07:24.215 --> 07:25.514
This meeting is adjourned.

07:32.957 --> 07:36.825
Well, you're right...
You're no victim.

07:36.860 --> 07:38.393
Daniel's a victim.
Margaux's a victim.

07:38.429 --> 07:39.828
They both needed this.

07:39.863 --> 07:41.063
Don't start.

07:41.098 --> 07:43.179
I voted for the wing,
and I just tried to save it.

07:43.202 --> 07:45.278
You should have told the truth
about Daniel.

07:45.302 --> 07:46.935
That was a decision
we all made together.

07:46.971 --> 07:48.003
I didn't want this.

07:48.038 --> 07:50.445
[ Scoffs ]
Feel free to delude yourself.

07:50.468 --> 07:51.840
But one thing I know

07:51.875 --> 07:53.875
is that you have
the blood of my son

07:53.911 --> 07:56.411
and my grandchild
on your hands.

08:02.680 --> 08:06.646
Sync, corrected by icephoenix
www.addic7ed.com

08:09.997 --> 08:12.192
Tony: The daycare center
is coming together nicely.

08:12.204 --> 08:15.170
Mm. It is. And we'll open
as soon as we pass inspection.

08:15.206 --> 08:16.271
But honestly, Tony,

08:16.307 --> 08:18.438
scheduling that has been
a red-tape nightmare.

08:18.461 --> 08:19.949
Well,
seven years in social services

08:19.985 --> 08:21.951
have taught me
that the wheels of government

08:21.987 --> 08:24.621
don't turn without a nudge or two.
I'll call.

08:24.656 --> 08:27.323
Oh, well, then,
my employees, members,

08:27.359 --> 08:31.180
and their soon-to-be
very well-cared-for children

08:31.204 --> 08:31.995
thank you.

08:32.030 --> 08:34.691
Well,
maybe you can show me how much.

08:34.715 --> 08:35.899
Come out with me tonight.

08:35.933 --> 08:39.174
I can't make up
any more excuses to drop by.

08:39.197 --> 08:40.537
Some friends of mine
are getting together...

08:40.572 --> 08:42.505
Just some drinks and good music
on the beach.

08:42.541 --> 08:45.647
Nothing like the bashes
I've heard that you're famous for,

08:45.671 --> 08:48.489
but you might enjoy yourself,
anyway.

08:48.513 --> 08:50.180
I think I might.

08:50.215 --> 08:51.681
Um...

08:51.716 --> 08:54.851
I... I'd have to just
make sure that I'm free.

08:54.886 --> 08:58.234
Well, my advice...
Be free.

09:09.641 --> 09:12.072
Looks like my social worker
made quite an impression.

09:13.936 --> 09:16.390
Is it that obvious?
[ Chuckles ]

09:16.413 --> 09:19.795
How does Louise feel about
splitting time with Tony?

09:19.818 --> 09:21.615
Um, fine.

09:24.249 --> 09:25.679
I guess.
[ Scoffs ]

09:25.702 --> 09:27.769
She doesn't know
she's splitting time with Tony.

09:30.218 --> 09:33.942
Jack, the truth is...

09:33.977 --> 09:35.677
I don't know how she'd react.

09:35.712 --> 09:38.847
She's been so fragile lately.

09:40.470 --> 09:42.317
And, honestly,
it just seems like

09:42.352 --> 09:44.519
things are getting
more complicated every day.

09:44.554 --> 09:47.188
[ Scoffs ]

09:47.224 --> 09:49.624
Look, I can tell you firsthand
that it sucks to find out

09:49.659 --> 09:51.192
that you've been
kept in the dark.

09:51.228 --> 09:53.728
And if she really is
as fragile as you're saying,

09:53.764 --> 09:55.663
then lying to her
is only gonna make it worse.

09:55.699 --> 09:58.560
All right, well,
speaking of Ems...

09:58.584 --> 10:01.217
Nice try. We're on <i>you</i>.

10:01.238 --> 10:03.338
Talk to your wife.

10:09.413 --> 10:12.353
So, uh,
now that you're a big-shot detective,

10:12.377 --> 10:15.059
maybe you can find
that 80 bucks you owe me.

10:15.094 --> 10:16.588
Can't solve 'em all, Willard.

10:16.612 --> 10:19.283
Certainly not at this pace.

10:20.284 --> 10:21.820
Victoria Grayson.

10:21.831 --> 10:23.867
I don't believe I've officially
had the pleasure.

10:23.903 --> 10:26.203
Well, it's only because you left me
waiting for over 30 minutes

10:26.238 --> 10:27.738
while you walked down
memory lane.

10:27.773 --> 10:29.873
There someone or something
that I can help you find?

10:29.909 --> 10:32.109
Like that sign out there
that says "Men Only"?

10:32.144 --> 10:33.844
Why don't you ask
your girlfriend

10:33.879 --> 10:35.880
how well I respond to sarcasm?

10:35.903 --> 10:38.118
Or maybe
I should ask your police chief

10:38.153 --> 10:40.253
what he thinks
about his newest detective

10:40.289 --> 10:42.789
dating a woman
who should be behind bars for fraud,

10:42.825 --> 10:44.310
among other things.

10:44.333 --> 10:47.928
And that you gave her
a <i>big</i> assist.

10:49.874 --> 10:51.553
Help me now,

10:51.576 --> 10:54.835
or your promotion will be
a blip of a memory.

10:59.708 --> 11:02.209
Bye, boys.

11:03.812 --> 11:06.174
Emily:
I have to clear Daniel's name.

11:06.198 --> 11:07.848
There'll be press
at the gala tomorrow.

11:07.883 --> 11:08.782
I'll do it there.

11:08.817 --> 11:10.083
You don't owe Victoria
anything.

11:10.118 --> 11:11.651
This has nothing to do
with Victoria.

11:11.687 --> 11:12.953
Her words mean nothing to me.

11:12.988 --> 11:14.788
But Margaux was reacting
to our lie.

11:16.058 --> 11:18.258
She lost her baby.

11:19.929 --> 11:21.428
I have to make it right.

11:21.463 --> 11:23.230
Listen, you have to stop blaming yourself,
Amanda.

11:23.265 --> 11:25.441
It was an accident.

11:25.464 --> 11:28.869
You didn't know Margaux
before all of this.

11:28.893 --> 11:32.038
Daniel's death changed her.

11:32.074 --> 11:34.508
She's trying to salvage the name
of someone that she loves,

11:34.543 --> 11:35.542
just like I did for you.

11:37.279 --> 11:40.046
You asked me
to leave revenge behind.

11:40.082 --> 11:42.215
This is what it looks like,
Dad.

11:43.354 --> 11:44.651
So,
what's with this desperate ploy

11:44.686 --> 11:45.718
to see the Lyman Ellis file?

11:45.742 --> 11:47.669
Lyman was
my friend and attorney.

11:47.705 --> 11:49.204
And we both know about
this precinct's,

11:49.239 --> 11:52.153
shall we say,
<i>subjective</i> police reporting.

11:52.176 --> 11:53.962
I wanted to make sure
the case was closed properly.

11:53.997 --> 11:56.531
Yeah, well, it was.
Closed it myself.

12:02.890 --> 12:05.390
Louise was the last person
to see him alive.

12:05.426 --> 12:08.393
My heart breaks for her.

12:10.130 --> 12:12.831
All that was found on Lyman
were his personal effects...

12:12.867 --> 12:15.507
His wallet, watch, kerchief?

12:15.531 --> 12:17.186
Nothing more?

12:17.210 --> 12:18.652
Look,
I don't know what you're up to,

12:18.687 --> 12:20.721
but it's damn sure
not about making sure

12:20.756 --> 12:22.918
that I closed my case properly.

12:22.942 --> 12:25.225
If I'm right,
this has something to do with Emily,

12:25.261 --> 12:26.910
which means you're gonna have
<i>me</i> to deal with, too.

12:26.928 --> 12:30.963
Oh. Drawing dramatic conclusions
from mere conjecture.

12:30.998 --> 12:33.399
Maybe this new job isn't right for you,
after all.

12:37.271 --> 12:39.271
How can I go with you
to the groundbreaking?

12:39.307 --> 12:41.073
I know you have
Ben's promotion party.

12:42.643 --> 12:44.710
Some of the rookies
still talk to me.

12:45.947 --> 12:47.046
I can do both.

12:50.051 --> 12:51.917
All right, so,
what would the new story be?

12:53.001 --> 12:55.187
Malcolm broke into my house
and tried to kill me.

12:55.222 --> 12:56.555
Daniel jumped
in front of the bullet,

12:56.591 --> 12:58.390
and Malcolm fled.

12:58.459 --> 13:01.427
The story is clean,
except for one thing.

13:01.462 --> 13:02.995
You need me
to recant my statement

13:03.030 --> 13:05.230
that you called me
about Daniel's attack.

13:06.807 --> 13:08.634
You can tell them
that I asked you to lie

13:08.669 --> 13:11.036
because I was afraid Malcolm
would come after me again,

13:11.072 --> 13:13.606
which he did.

13:13.641 --> 13:16.175
[ Sighs ]
I know it's a lot to ask.

13:17.812 --> 13:20.779
Things between us have been...

13:20.815 --> 13:22.181
Awkward?

13:23.384 --> 13:24.750
[ Sighs ]

13:25.720 --> 13:28.229
I don't know. I...
I thought we put all this to bed already.

13:29.485 --> 13:30.656
I killed someone.

13:30.691 --> 13:32.524
And <i>I</i> will protect you.

13:32.560 --> 13:34.593
Jack, I wouldn't ask you this

13:34.629 --> 13:37.196
if I wasn't absolutely sure
that I could.

13:40.636 --> 13:41.935
I got to think about it.

13:41.970 --> 13:42.903
[ Door opens ]

13:42.938 --> 13:45.107
Stevie: <i>I</i> don't.

13:45.130 --> 13:47.040
Over my dead body.

13:48.776 --> 13:51.578
- I see how you work, Emily.
- Excuse me?

13:51.613 --> 13:53.647
I know you brought me to town
last year as a pawn

13:53.682 --> 13:55.582
in your vendetta
against the Graysons.

13:55.617 --> 13:57.751
I risked my sobriety to help.

13:57.786 --> 13:59.486
You clearly manipulated me.

13:59.521 --> 14:01.321
- I draw the line at my son.
- Mom!

14:01.356 --> 14:04.558
- I have always protected Jack.
- Really?

14:04.593 --> 14:06.793
He almost lost custody of Carl
because of you.

14:06.829 --> 14:08.929
He almost lost Carl
because of a decision

14:08.964 --> 14:10.897
that we all made together...
We didn't have a choice.

14:10.933 --> 14:11.832
All right, enough!

14:11.867 --> 14:13.884
You are a train wreck, Emily.

14:13.908 --> 14:17.912
Jack will not be
your collateral damage again.

14:17.935 --> 14:19.840
I take responsibility
for the things I've done,

14:19.875 --> 14:22.229
but I was not alone in this.

14:22.253 --> 14:26.346
If I have anything to say,
you <i>will</i> be alone going forward.

14:29.813 --> 14:32.831
It's been years since I had
a homemade lemon tart.

14:32.854 --> 14:34.871
It's been just as long
since I've made one.

14:34.907 --> 14:37.493
But you were so good to me
after Daniel's passing

14:37.513 --> 14:39.045
that I thought
I'd return the kindness

14:39.081 --> 14:40.446
when I heard about Lyman.

14:42.050 --> 14:44.150
You're very sweet.

14:44.186 --> 14:47.066
But you have
a lot on your plate yourself.

14:47.078 --> 14:49.990
I read that article.
The media can be cruel.

14:50.025 --> 14:51.669
Yes, well,
I'll handle the press,

14:51.692 --> 14:54.957
and I'll defend Daniel
until the day I die.

14:54.980 --> 14:56.763
You never turn your back
on your children.

14:58.800 --> 15:00.100
After Daniel died,

15:00.135 --> 15:02.963
all these memories
came flooding back

15:02.987 --> 15:06.462
every time I saw a picture
or heard an old voice-mail...

15:07.943 --> 15:09.703
Or handled his belongings.

15:14.550 --> 15:16.149
I can help you
with Lyman's things

15:16.184 --> 15:17.317
if you need me to.

15:20.856 --> 15:22.856
Well...

15:22.891 --> 15:25.626
I didn't think you were here
for my darjeeling.

15:25.650 --> 15:26.760
You're here
for the very same reason

15:26.795 --> 15:27.961
that my late brother was,

15:27.996 --> 15:29.996
and that is to hurt Nolan
with that flash drive.

15:30.032 --> 15:31.311
[ Chuckles ]

15:31.336 --> 15:33.236
I am here
because I care about you.

15:33.271 --> 15:36.079
Take your things
and leave my home right now.

15:37.100 --> 15:40.376
I can't believe
I almost fell for your sympathy.

15:41.720 --> 15:43.637
You're trusting
the wrong people.

15:43.673 --> 15:45.406
Nolan hasn't told you
everything.

15:45.441 --> 15:46.974
Nolan and I have no secrets.

15:49.887 --> 15:52.095
Did he tell you what happened
the night Daniel died?

15:54.680 --> 15:56.550
The people to whom
you've pledged your loyalty

15:56.585 --> 15:57.918
have two faces,

15:57.953 --> 15:59.319
and you...

15:59.355 --> 16:01.225
You've got a good heart.

16:02.591 --> 16:04.324
Don't let them break it.

16:08.931 --> 16:10.564
[ Scoffs ]

16:12.101 --> 16:13.811
You were unfair to Emily.

16:13.835 --> 16:16.770
She's been unfair to <i>you</i>
over and over.

16:17.973 --> 16:20.240
Clearing Daniel's name
isn't just about

16:20.276 --> 16:21.475
you helping a friend.

16:21.510 --> 16:22.910
There are legal ramifications.

16:22.945 --> 16:25.826
- I was a cop. I know that.
- Then let's play this out.

16:25.850 --> 16:28.782
You corroborate Emily's story.

16:28.818 --> 16:30.384
Police could start
kicking over cans,

16:30.419 --> 16:31.385
and you go down

16:31.420 --> 16:32.853
for obstruction of justice
and murder,

16:32.888 --> 16:33.987
which is a capital offense.

16:34.023 --> 16:36.390
- And she was an FBI agent.
- Who was pointing a gun at me.

16:36.425 --> 16:39.262
<i>Exactly</i> what you should
have said that night.

16:39.274 --> 16:42.115
The self-defense ship
has sailed.

16:43.099 --> 16:44.231
What about Carl?

16:44.266 --> 16:46.789
Carl's a reason to come clean.

16:46.812 --> 16:49.002
Margaux came after us
because of the lie about Daniel.

16:49.038 --> 16:50.104
This is my mess, too.

16:50.139 --> 16:52.239
The only reason
you're even considering this

16:52.274 --> 16:54.775
is because of
how you feel about her.

16:57.280 --> 16:58.112
Does she know?

16:58.147 --> 16:59.513
She knows.

17:01.284 --> 17:03.221
I'm past that.

17:03.245 --> 17:04.484
You positive?

17:07.214 --> 17:08.255
[ Drawer opens ]

17:08.290 --> 17:10.124
[ Sighs ]

17:10.159 --> 17:12.358
You come from
two alcoholic parents.

17:13.628 --> 17:15.996
Make sure Emily's
not your glass of scotch.

17:21.237 --> 17:22.903
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

17:29.178 --> 17:30.711
You do know that, uh,

17:30.746 --> 17:32.446
breaking
the open-container law...

17:32.481 --> 17:34.457
It's...
It's a gateway crime.

17:34.480 --> 17:35.848
Told you I had a bad side.

17:35.883 --> 17:37.750
[ Laughs ]

17:38.530 --> 17:39.885
And an empty glass.

17:39.921 --> 17:42.188
I'll be right back.

17:45.097 --> 17:46.897
I'm really glad you came.

17:51.837 --> 17:55.405
[ Cellphone ringing ]

18:06.051 --> 18:08.151
[ Dialing ]

18:08.187 --> 18:09.052
[ Ringing ]

18:09.087 --> 18:10.053
<i>Hi. It's Louise.</i>

18:10.122 --> 18:11.655
<i>Leave a message.
[ Beep ]</i>

18:11.690 --> 18:14.691
Hey, um, Louise, sorry,
I just missed your call.

18:14.726 --> 18:16.526
You're probably
leaving a message.

18:16.562 --> 18:17.527
Um...

18:19.451 --> 18:22.245
I'm swamped at the club, so...
[Laughs]

18:22.269 --> 18:24.367
I'm... I'm probably gonna
be here pretty late.

18:24.403 --> 18:25.936
You don't need to wait up.

18:25.971 --> 18:27.437
I'll see you in the morning.

18:30.869 --> 18:34.403
Before I jump to conclusions,
does "swamped at the club"

18:34.439 --> 18:37.473
mean something
other than the obvious?

18:37.509 --> 18:40.476
It's... Tony, um...

18:40.512 --> 18:41.611
The thing with Louise...

18:41.646 --> 18:43.042
It's not
a traditional marriage.

18:43.054 --> 18:45.114
Then why lie to her?

18:47.558 --> 18:49.352
This isn't how I work, Nolan.

18:49.387 --> 18:52.255
I won't be the other man
in someone's marriage.

18:55.460 --> 18:57.326
Okay, I just...

18:57.362 --> 18:58.728
[ Chuckles ]

18:58.763 --> 19:01.664
I just need some time to,
you know, figure things out.

19:01.699 --> 19:03.366
That's the thing about being honest,
Nolan.

19:03.401 --> 19:04.333
You <i>don't</i>.

19:06.318 --> 19:09.839
You ever figure things out,
call me.

19:18.116 --> 19:21.250
Right.
We are almost there.

19:21.286 --> 19:24.754
No, no, no, no.
I'll do the cooking, baby bro.

19:24.789 --> 19:26.956
Last time you manned the grill,
we had to order Chinese.

19:26.991 --> 19:28.457
You're just never gonna
let me forget that.

19:28.493 --> 19:29.625
It ranks right up there

19:29.661 --> 19:31.994
with the time you taught
yourself the art of kissing.

19:32.030 --> 19:32.995
Wow.
[ Laughs ]

19:33.031 --> 19:35.246
Really, Kev?
In front of the girl?

19:35.269 --> 19:36.936
- Cease and desist.
- No, no, no.

19:36.948 --> 19:38.566
I need dirt on you.

19:38.589 --> 19:40.209
Kevin, spill.

19:40.233 --> 19:44.436
No.
I think I'm gonna keep my best stuff

19:44.460 --> 19:45.840
for Ben's big party
tomorrow night.

19:45.875 --> 19:47.775
Yeah, well,
I can't wait for that.

19:47.810 --> 19:49.176
What about you, Emily?

19:49.212 --> 19:50.578
You have
an annoying brother like me?

19:50.613 --> 19:51.679
[ Chuckles ]

19:51.714 --> 19:54.949
Um, no, I'm a...
I'm an only child, actually.

19:54.984 --> 19:56.584
I bet you had your dad
wrapped around your finger,

19:56.619 --> 19:57.685
just like my little girl does.

19:57.720 --> 19:58.853
[ Chuckles ]

19:58.888 --> 20:00.521
We're close.

20:00.556 --> 20:02.156
I mean...

20:02.191 --> 20:03.257
We <i>were</i> close.

20:03.292 --> 20:04.425
I, uh...

20:04.460 --> 20:06.754
I lost my parents
when I was young.

20:06.778 --> 20:09.279
They died in a car crash.

20:09.302 --> 20:10.865
Oh.

20:10.900 --> 20:11.999
I'm, uh...

20:12.035 --> 20:14.660
I'm sorry to hear that.

20:14.683 --> 20:16.604
Tell you what,
why don't you let me handle the talking?

20:16.639 --> 20:19.216
You stick to what you know
and go check that grill.

20:22.979 --> 20:23.978
[ Doorbell rings ]

20:24.013 --> 20:26.338
Oh. Sorry.
I'll get that.

20:28.877 --> 20:30.317
- Jack.
- Hey.

20:32.829 --> 20:34.529
You've got company.

20:34.564 --> 20:36.464
Yeah. It's fine.
Come in.

20:36.500 --> 20:38.333
[ Sighs ]

20:43.433 --> 20:44.665
You talk to your mom?

20:46.736 --> 20:47.701
[ Sighs ]

20:47.737 --> 20:49.437
[ Chuckles ]

20:49.472 --> 20:51.238
And you're not gonna help me.

20:51.274 --> 20:52.940
I can't. I'm sorry.

20:52.975 --> 20:54.175
It's just too risky.

20:54.210 --> 20:56.110
The cops are gonna
turn your story over and over

20:56.145 --> 20:57.111
looking for holes.

20:57.146 --> 20:58.846
And I will have answers
for them.

20:58.881 --> 21:00.948
I've gotten away with
bigger things than this.

21:00.983 --> 21:02.516
No one knows that
better than me.

21:05.288 --> 21:06.387
[ Sighs ]

21:06.422 --> 21:08.823
If you don't back my story,
the plan is dead.

21:08.858 --> 21:10.608
Then it's dead.

21:10.620 --> 21:12.946
I got to think
about Carl and...

21:12.982 --> 21:14.047
And you.

21:15.718 --> 21:16.997
I'm not doing anything

21:17.033 --> 21:18.265
to put the people that I love
in jeopardy.

21:18.301 --> 21:20.630
Kevin:
Ready to put the burgers on.

21:20.653 --> 21:21.635
Oh.

21:21.671 --> 21:24.508
- Hey, man.
- Hey.

21:24.525 --> 21:27.826
Um, Jack, this is,
uh, Kevin, Ben's brother.

21:27.862 --> 21:28.875
Porter.

21:28.899 --> 21:31.329
I've heard a lot about you.

21:31.353 --> 21:32.534
Well, I...
I don't mean to interrupt.

21:32.569 --> 21:34.332
I just need to know
how Emily takes hers.

21:34.355 --> 21:35.752
Rare.

21:35.776 --> 21:37.739
The bluer, the better.

21:43.314 --> 21:44.813
Let it go, Ems.

21:53.157 --> 21:55.190
[ Sighs ]

21:59.085 --> 22:01.680
You want to tell me
about last night?

22:01.704 --> 22:04.663
What was going one
at the beach club?

22:04.686 --> 22:06.353
Oh, um...

22:06.388 --> 22:08.588
It turned out it was nothing,
so...

22:08.624 --> 22:09.890
Okay.

22:09.925 --> 22:12.325
'Cause there's absolutely no
reason for you to go into work

22:12.361 --> 22:14.027
before the sun
is comfortable in the sky.

22:14.062 --> 22:15.228
[ Chuckles ]

22:15.264 --> 22:16.329
Stay!

22:16.365 --> 22:19.297
Let's watch trashy TV
and get day-drunk

22:19.320 --> 22:21.199
and finish our talk.

22:21.223 --> 22:27.030
Well, that does sound indulgent,
but, uh, duty calls, so...

22:27.053 --> 22:30.710
Well, I guess I'll just keep
reading gossip rags all day.

22:30.746 --> 22:32.212
You know, I can't believe

22:32.247 --> 22:34.376
how many articles
are still trashing Daniel.

22:34.399 --> 22:39.354
It's so hard for me to imagine him
attacking Emily like that.

22:39.378 --> 22:41.321
You didn't know him
for that long.

22:42.457 --> 22:44.024
I guess.

22:44.059 --> 22:46.693
But I just met <i>you</i>,
and I know you.

22:46.728 --> 22:48.161
Which is exactly
what I told Victoria

22:48.196 --> 22:49.963
when she dropped in yesterday.

22:53.141 --> 22:54.040
She was here?

22:54.075 --> 22:56.109
She came to pay her respects,

22:56.144 --> 22:59.587
five minutes in,
she spun it into her usual vitriol,

22:59.605 --> 23:00.838
so I threw her out.

23:03.176 --> 23:05.694
You know, when we get the baby,
we should install a gate

23:05.730 --> 23:07.329
to keep the hyenas
from dropping in

23:07.365 --> 23:08.683
with store-bought
lemon tart.

23:08.706 --> 23:10.281
[ Chuckles ]

23:11.501 --> 23:14.985
I... I know you're still thinking
about the baby.

23:15.021 --> 23:17.054
[ Sighs ]

23:17.090 --> 23:18.589
I am.

23:18.624 --> 23:22.493
And, uh,
I'm about to be late, so...

23:22.528 --> 23:24.327
Call me later?

23:25.364 --> 23:26.797
Yeah, of course.

23:29.202 --> 23:31.702
[ Sighs ]

23:31.738 --> 23:33.637
[ Groans ]

23:36.671 --> 23:38.647
_

23:40.824 --> 23:43.438
_

23:48.821 --> 23:53.017
Sorry to intrude,
but you haven't been returning my calls.

23:53.029 --> 23:55.431
I finally made progress
in the White Gold matter.

23:57.368 --> 24:00.469
With all that's happened,
I had forgotten about my inquiry.

24:00.504 --> 24:02.171
She sent word
through one of her associates.

24:02.206 --> 24:03.705
She is stateside

24:03.741 --> 24:05.841
and has agreed to take care
of your Emily Thorne problem.

24:05.876 --> 24:08.310
Don't pursue it any further.

24:09.647 --> 24:11.013
With all due respect,

24:11.048 --> 24:14.650
don't let what just happened to you
cloud your judgment.

24:16.138 --> 24:20.155
<i>L'arreter tu maintenant...</i>
I don't want Emily hurt.

24:21.039 --> 24:22.658
The wheels are in motion.

24:22.693 --> 24:24.359
I already transferred the money

24:24.395 --> 24:25.694
to the designated
Cayman account,

24:25.729 --> 24:27.796
and her point person
has gone dark.

24:27.832 --> 24:29.131
We have no way to reach her.

24:29.166 --> 24:31.086
No,
<i>you</i> have no way to reach her.

24:31.109 --> 24:34.644
If you ever
question my judgment again,

24:34.667 --> 24:37.139
I'll make sure
she finds you next.

24:42.746 --> 24:44.813
You're here early.

24:44.849 --> 24:46.323
[ Chuckles ]

24:46.347 --> 24:47.249
Well, uh, my beach body

24:47.284 --> 24:50.552
couldn't survive another
Southern-fried breakfast, and...

24:50.588 --> 24:51.753
Wait, what's up?

24:51.789 --> 24:55.629
I know you're not here
to reserve a primo cabana, so...

24:55.652 --> 24:59.750
I asked Jack to help me
clear Daniel's name.

24:59.774 --> 25:01.251
He said no.

25:01.286 --> 25:03.586
Whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Slow down.

25:03.622 --> 25:06.856
Why would you want to open
that can of Grayson worms?

25:08.116 --> 25:09.348
For Margaux?

25:11.486 --> 25:13.292
'Cause of the baby?

25:13.315 --> 25:16.022
Ems, I know you feel bad,
but Jack was right.

25:16.057 --> 25:17.223
Do you know what could happen?

25:17.258 --> 25:18.624
You'd think after four years,

25:18.660 --> 25:20.359
you guys would have
a little faith that I <i>do</i>.

25:20.395 --> 25:21.661
Well...

25:21.696 --> 25:25.498
Look, I just need to erase Jack
from the narrative.

25:25.533 --> 25:26.566
Can you help me?

25:26.601 --> 25:29.011
Look, I have many skills,

25:29.034 --> 25:32.862
but I can't manipulate
what people <i>have</i> heard... Yet.

25:32.873 --> 25:36.075
I know. I just
thought it would inspire something.

25:36.111 --> 25:38.144
Yeah,
like abandoning this crazy idea.

25:38.179 --> 25:40.680
Nolan,
I have to do something good.

25:43.875 --> 25:47.453
I... I mean this in the best possible way,
but...

25:47.489 --> 25:50.991
Emily Thorne
was not built for good.

25:51.014 --> 25:53.386
She was built
to clear her dad's name,

25:53.422 --> 25:55.922
which she did...
Brilliantly.

25:59.294 --> 26:00.660
So there's nothing you can do?

26:00.695 --> 26:01.761
Yeah... I can tell you

26:01.797 --> 26:04.297
to enjoy the perks
of being a beloved socialite

26:04.332 --> 26:05.817
who's earned them.

26:09.150 --> 26:11.271
Stevie: David.

26:11.306 --> 26:12.672
Stevie.

26:12.707 --> 26:15.345
[ Chuckles lightly ]
That's a nice surprise.

26:15.369 --> 26:18.478
- We need to talk about Emily.
- Yeah.

26:18.513 --> 26:21.614
You know what,
you were right the other day

26:21.650 --> 26:23.149
when you told me
she'd come around.

26:23.185 --> 26:25.205
Things between us are better.

26:25.229 --> 26:27.388
Oh.
Great for the two of you.

26:27.389 --> 26:29.289
But keep her away from Jack.

26:29.324 --> 26:32.602
[ Chuckles ]
Where's that coming from?

26:32.614 --> 26:34.694
She asked him
to change his story

26:34.729 --> 26:36.671
to help her clear Daniel's name.

26:36.694 --> 26:39.122
I talked him out of it,
but what about the next time

26:39.145 --> 26:41.106
when she asks him to do
something reckless?

26:41.130 --> 26:42.903
Emily wanted to do
the right thing.

26:42.939 --> 26:44.385
- You knew?
- Yeah.

26:44.408 --> 26:45.340
[ Scoffs ]

26:45.363 --> 26:48.921
She suddenly gets a conscience
and Jack's supposed to hop to?

26:48.945 --> 26:51.986
Did you really think that ill-conceived plan
was a good idea?

26:52.021 --> 26:55.275
No, I didn't,
but Emily's been on her own a long time.

26:55.299 --> 26:56.743
I don't have a right
to force my way.

26:56.755 --> 26:59.420
You have every right.
You're her father.

26:59.443 --> 27:01.118
Don't shirk
your responsibilities

27:01.153 --> 27:03.231
because you feel guilty
about her childhood.

27:03.255 --> 27:04.676
You're out of line.

27:04.699 --> 27:06.457
You don't know a thing
about our relationship.

27:06.492 --> 27:08.233
I know enough!

27:08.256 --> 27:10.427
Stop fixing this damn boat

27:10.463 --> 27:13.917
and take responsibility for
the fire you lit 20 years ago!

27:13.940 --> 27:16.166
Conrad framed you
for Flight 197,

27:16.202 --> 27:18.002
but you slept with his wife
first.

27:18.037 --> 27:20.237
Your bad choices
knocked over the first domino.

27:20.272 --> 27:21.438
I got work to do.

27:21.474 --> 27:23.841
- So that's it?
- Yeah, that's it.

27:23.876 --> 27:25.009
We've both made mistakes,

27:25.044 --> 27:26.810
but you don't have a right
to crucify me for mine.

27:26.846 --> 27:28.847
That's the end
of the conversation.

27:28.870 --> 27:30.481
- Ow!
- Oh! David!

27:30.516 --> 27:31.682
[ Grunts ]

27:35.588 --> 27:38.689
Emily wanted to redeem Grayson.

27:38.724 --> 27:41.726
These really must be
the end times.

27:42.689 --> 27:44.194
Well, thank the revenge gods
you said no,

27:44.230 --> 27:47.808
'cause there could have been
major fallout for both of you.

27:47.832 --> 27:49.115
I know.

27:50.324 --> 27:52.685
You want to know the truth?

27:52.708 --> 27:54.751
I almost said yes
when she asked me.

27:56.976 --> 27:58.300
I know, Jack.

27:59.845 --> 28:02.046
And on top of it,
Daniel saved Emily's life,

28:02.081 --> 28:04.055
and we destroyed
his reputation.

28:04.079 --> 28:05.482
And I still don't know
what's best for Carl

28:05.518 --> 28:06.984
'cause Emily's plan
could land me in jail.

28:07.019 --> 28:08.919
But the cover-up about Daniel
almost did the same thing.

28:08.954 --> 28:10.287
Okay, Jack.

28:10.322 --> 28:11.221
[ Sighs ]

28:11.257 --> 28:13.804
Don't let sleeping lies
dog you.

28:13.828 --> 28:15.893
There's some bells
that can't be un-rung,

28:15.928 --> 28:18.562
like the one that got me
to church on time.

28:20.228 --> 28:22.342
You still haven't
talked to Louise?

28:23.169 --> 28:24.159
No.

28:24.182 --> 28:25.969
I mean, what's the point?

28:26.005 --> 28:29.951
Things were over with Tony
before they even began,

28:29.974 --> 28:32.643
and...
Louise is too broken right now.

28:32.678 --> 28:34.812
So you stay unhappily married?

28:34.847 --> 28:36.948
For how long?

28:36.972 --> 28:38.816
Why does she have
such a hold over you?

28:45.243 --> 28:48.989
You remember when I said that
she was emotionally fragile?

28:49.012 --> 28:50.680
Yeah.

28:50.703 --> 28:54.925
Her brother Lyman's death
wasn't entirely an accident.

28:54.949 --> 28:57.134
She caught him snooping
on my laptop.

28:57.169 --> 28:59.103
They got into a fight.

28:59.138 --> 29:00.270
He slipped.

29:00.306 --> 29:03.170
She let him fall to protect me.

29:04.710 --> 29:06.743
I've just had this growing knot
in my stomach

29:06.779 --> 29:09.546
ever since she told me,
and now...

29:09.582 --> 29:11.558
She wants to have a baby.

29:11.582 --> 29:16.753
Like, I want a family
and a real marriage one day, but...

29:16.789 --> 29:18.789
[ Chuckles ]

29:18.824 --> 29:21.225
With somebody stable.

29:21.260 --> 29:22.826
Not someone who...

29:22.862 --> 29:24.895
Not someone you pity.

29:26.665 --> 29:28.365
Sounds awful.

29:28.400 --> 29:31.502
But...

29:31.537 --> 29:33.504
Yeah.

29:45.238 --> 29:47.385
How did you figure out
who I am?

29:47.399 --> 29:49.548
Your Cayman account helped.

29:49.571 --> 29:52.341
The LeMarchal name carries a lot
of weight in the Caribbean,

29:52.376 --> 29:54.766
especially
in the black markets.

29:54.790 --> 29:57.679
So once I knew your alias...

29:59.250 --> 30:01.550
I need to cancel
the Thorne job.

30:02.520 --> 30:04.186
Your associate
went to great lengths

30:04.221 --> 30:05.821
to persuade me
to take this job...

30:05.856 --> 30:07.673
And failed.

30:07.696 --> 30:09.691
But when I found out
who he was working for,

30:09.727 --> 30:11.319
how could I say no?

30:11.343 --> 30:13.984
I love a kick-ass,
powerful kind of girl.

30:14.008 --> 30:16.514
I wasn't myself
when I asked him to hire you.

30:16.537 --> 30:18.426
You were
the darkest part of yourself.

30:18.462 --> 30:20.328
Don't be ashamed.
Own it.

30:20.363 --> 30:22.030
Oh, I am nothing like you.

30:22.065 --> 30:24.365
[ Sighs ]
You want me to cancel?

30:24.401 --> 30:25.700
Fine.

30:25.735 --> 30:28.863
But I still have one issue...
You know my real identity.

30:28.869 --> 30:32.003
And since my anonymity
is important to me,

30:32.039 --> 30:34.105
you and I have a problem.

30:34.141 --> 30:37.175
If anything happens to me,
an e-mail will be sent

30:37.211 --> 30:39.678
outing your real identity
to Interpol.

30:39.713 --> 30:41.879
[ Chuckling ]
You're threatening me.

30:41.902 --> 30:44.349
You're risking your life
to save your enemy's?

30:44.384 --> 30:48.241
I have nothing left to lose
but my soul.

30:48.264 --> 30:51.756
And I'm not willing
to give that up just yet.

30:56.486 --> 30:58.052
[ Door opens ]

31:00.523 --> 31:01.689
[ Door closes ]

31:03.760 --> 31:05.262
Louise?

31:07.664 --> 31:08.896
Louise!

31:08.931 --> 31:10.331
Louise!

31:10.366 --> 31:12.136
Oh, God.

31:12.160 --> 31:13.522
Are you okay?

31:13.545 --> 31:14.620
You scared me.

31:14.655 --> 31:17.290
I'm a big girl, Nolan.

31:17.313 --> 31:20.753
I can swim in the deep end
alone.

31:20.777 --> 31:23.301
Guess you didn't have to
work late tonight.

31:23.325 --> 31:25.146
No.

31:25.181 --> 31:26.280
Thought we could talk.

31:34.223 --> 31:37.291
Now, is this about my sudden
outbreak of baby fever?

31:40.763 --> 31:42.029
It is about us.

31:45.635 --> 31:48.069
I think it's time that we...

31:48.104 --> 31:49.962
End this marriage.

31:49.985 --> 31:53.107
We got into this to liberate you
from your family,

31:53.142 --> 31:54.742
which we did.

31:54.777 --> 31:56.977
But...

31:57.013 --> 32:00.081
I mean, I'm just worried
that the longer we stay in this,

32:00.116 --> 32:03.896
the more
blurred lines are gonna get.

32:06.632 --> 32:09.323
Lou-Lou, say something.

32:11.728 --> 32:14.984
We both agreed
that this would be temporary.

32:15.007 --> 32:17.798
A fun summer of debauchery.

32:20.802 --> 32:22.837
I guess I just...

32:22.872 --> 32:25.024
Got a little carried away
with playing house.

32:31.314 --> 32:33.704
I'll call the lawyers
in the morning,

32:34.643 --> 32:36.783
and...
I'll be out of here as soon as I can.

32:36.806 --> 32:37.885
There's no rush.

32:37.920 --> 32:40.788
We'll always be friends...
Forever.

32:40.823 --> 32:41.893
[ Chuckles ]

32:41.916 --> 32:43.995
How can we be anything but?

32:45.134 --> 32:47.728
You're my knight in Versace armor,
right?

32:47.764 --> 32:48.929
Hm.
[ Chuckles ]

32:50.466 --> 32:54.702
And thank you
for being completely honest with me.

33:07.049 --> 33:10.117
[ Grunting ]

33:16.077 --> 33:17.768
Hey,
I thought you'd be dressed.

33:17.792 --> 33:19.960
We were gonna get a bite to eat
with Kevin before the party.

33:19.996 --> 33:22.429
I think I should stay home.

33:22.465 --> 33:24.231
You and I
can celebrate together later.

33:24.267 --> 33:26.600
Okay, okay, hey, what's...
What's... What's going on?

33:26.636 --> 33:27.968
[ Breathing heavily ]

33:28.004 --> 33:30.439
You've been different
since Jack showed up.

33:31.156 --> 33:34.452
Kevin said you two were in
a pretty intense conversation.

33:34.488 --> 33:35.720
I wasn't gonna ask.

33:35.738 --> 33:38.826
Look, I asked Jack
to help me clear Daniel's name.

33:38.850 --> 33:41.615
Don't. I've already heard all of
the reasons why it's a bad idea.

33:41.651 --> 33:43.017
Not from <i>me</i> you haven't,

33:43.052 --> 33:45.419
since you didn't even think
to discuss it.

33:47.590 --> 33:49.623
[ Scoffs ]

33:49.659 --> 33:51.343
You know,
a little heads-up

33:51.366 --> 33:52.493
that the girl I'm dating
was gonna retract

33:52.528 --> 33:54.195
a statement she made
in a case that I closed

33:54.230 --> 33:56.028
would have been nice,

33:56.052 --> 33:57.770
seeing how it could
affect my job.

33:57.794 --> 33:59.266
Look, I would have told you.

33:59.302 --> 34:00.634
When?
After you figured it out with Jack?

34:00.670 --> 34:03.270
Oh, don't make this
about something that it's not.

34:03.306 --> 34:05.139
Then don't pretend
it's nothing.

34:05.174 --> 34:06.440
I know that it's not about him.

34:06.475 --> 34:08.242
I know this is about
what happened to Margaux.

34:08.277 --> 34:10.556
This is about <i>everything</i>.

34:10.580 --> 34:13.780
People have gotten hurt and died
because of all of this.

34:13.803 --> 34:15.416
So much has happened
that can't be undone.

34:15.451 --> 34:18.877
This one thing...
This <i>one</i> thing I wanted to undo.

34:18.900 --> 34:20.120
With another lie?

34:20.156 --> 34:21.288
This other story

34:21.324 --> 34:23.135
is just gonna be like
a snake chasing its own tail.

34:23.158 --> 34:25.155
Yeah, I know that, Ben.

34:25.178 --> 34:27.194
I live between two worlds.

34:27.230 --> 34:29.263
You couldn't possibly
understand.

34:29.297 --> 34:31.389
Yeah, but I want to.

34:31.400 --> 34:34.034
Oh, come on. Don't do that.
Don't shut me out.

34:37.440 --> 34:40.456
[ Sighing ]
You should go to your party.

34:40.480 --> 34:42.524
And you should come with me.

34:42.547 --> 34:44.612
It might be nice for you
to be around a bunch of people

34:44.647 --> 34:47.047
who expect nothing from you
but to have a good time.

34:47.083 --> 34:48.322
[ Sighs ]

34:48.333 --> 34:51.552
With me
at the head of that line.

34:51.587 --> 34:52.620
Ben.

34:52.655 --> 34:57.091
Look, I can see who you are,
Emily.

34:57.126 --> 34:58.225
That's not a lie.

35:03.243 --> 35:05.532
I hope you change your mind.

35:10.139 --> 35:13.607
[ Door opens, closes ]

35:17.616 --> 35:19.101
[ Knock on door ]

35:22.307 --> 35:24.634
[ Laughing ]
You still have your hand.

35:24.646 --> 35:26.042
Yeah, I cut myself pretty deep,

35:26.077 --> 35:28.177
but Dr. Raffin said
there wasn't any real damage,

35:28.213 --> 35:29.579
so you didn't have to come by.

35:29.614 --> 35:30.783
I feel responsible.

35:30.803 --> 35:32.736
I shouldn't have
attacked you earlier.

35:35.644 --> 35:37.641
Our kids aren't kids, Stevie.

35:37.677 --> 35:39.743
We can't hold their hand.

35:39.779 --> 35:41.645
I know, but...

35:41.681 --> 35:44.381
Jack's been so reckless
when it comes to Emily.

35:44.417 --> 35:45.616
It scares me.

35:45.651 --> 35:48.352
Emily's his kryptonite,
just like Victoria was yours.

35:48.387 --> 35:50.643
Emily's not Victoria.

35:50.666 --> 35:52.498
I hope to God you're right.

35:56.426 --> 35:58.398
- Glad you're okay.
- Yeah.

36:07.640 --> 36:10.274
You look beautiful.

36:12.344 --> 36:13.410
You came.

36:14.914 --> 36:16.447
You were right.

36:16.471 --> 36:17.281
Your new plan's the only way

36:17.316 --> 36:18.816
to keep the police
from looking under rocks.

36:18.851 --> 36:21.418
And despite everything
that we've been through lately,

36:21.454 --> 36:23.787
I'm not letting you
do this alone.

36:25.391 --> 36:27.791
And besides,
I'm a sucker for a groundbreaking.

36:27.827 --> 36:28.992
[ Chuckles ]

36:32.734 --> 36:34.367
I'm ready.

36:36.402 --> 36:38.202
Are you?

36:48.380 --> 36:50.748
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

36:52.485 --> 36:54.752
Kevin: And while I'm not
totally comfortable

36:54.787 --> 36:57.136
getting lit
with a bunch of cops,

36:57.159 --> 37:00.189
I am honored to raise a glass
to my brother's friends,

37:00.224 --> 37:02.992
who I pray
help him close cases,

37:03.027 --> 37:04.961
because he can't find his ass
with both hands.

37:04.996 --> 37:07.096
[ Laughter ]

37:07.131 --> 37:08.764
To Detective Hunter.

37:08.800 --> 37:11.500
- Detective Hunter.
- Cheers. Cheers.

37:14.872 --> 37:16.405
Ahh.

37:16.441 --> 37:17.740
- Proud of you, bro.
- Thanks, man.

37:19.210 --> 37:20.876
[ Laughter ]

37:22.643 --> 37:24.626
If you're looking
for your girl,

37:24.661 --> 37:26.895
maybe you should
check with your ex-partner.

37:26.930 --> 37:29.037
Look, I told you...
They're just friends.

37:29.061 --> 37:30.728
She and Jack go way back.

37:30.751 --> 37:32.583
There's nothing more to it.

37:37.012 --> 37:38.494
You sure about that?

37:47.898 --> 37:50.260
_

37:53.865 --> 37:56.749
It is because of the generosity
of many donors

37:56.784 --> 37:58.964
that we're able to break ground

37:58.985 --> 38:02.887
for the new research wing here
at Southampton Medical Center.

38:03.543 --> 38:05.633
Without further ado...

38:09.563 --> 38:11.362
[ Laughter,
cheers and applause ]

38:11.398 --> 38:14.866
Terrific job.
Very, very exciting.

38:18.418 --> 38:19.317
May I?

38:19.352 --> 38:23.122
Ms. Thorne,
I've already spoken on behalf of the board.

38:23.145 --> 38:26.091
I've been very generous with
this hospital over the years.

38:26.126 --> 38:29.034
That should buy me five minutes at the podium,
don't you think?

38:29.903 --> 38:31.371
Of course.

38:38.552 --> 38:40.079
Good evening.

38:45.145 --> 38:48.025
We're all aware of the scandal

38:48.049 --> 38:51.649
casting a shadow
over tonight's announcement.

38:51.685 --> 38:54.419
The board elected
not to name the research wing

38:54.454 --> 38:55.687
after my ex-husband

38:55.722 --> 38:59.541
because people believe
that he broke into my house

38:59.564 --> 39:02.831
and tried to attack me.

39:02.855 --> 39:05.864
That is the story
that I told that night.

39:08.668 --> 39:10.101
But none of it is true.

39:11.371 --> 39:13.404
The truth...

39:14.229 --> 39:16.474
Is that Malcolm Black
was my attacker.

39:16.510 --> 39:19.344
[ Crowd murmuring ]

39:20.059 --> 39:21.879
He tried to kill me.

39:24.017 --> 39:27.252
<i>And Daniel Grayson
took a bullet</i>

39:27.287 --> 39:28.853
<i>that was meant for me.</i>

39:28.889 --> 39:31.030
<i>[ Crowd gasps ]</i>

39:31.053 --> 39:33.740
<i>That night,</i>

39:33.764 --> 39:35.836
<i>Daniel saved my life.</i>

39:35.871 --> 39:38.672
<i>[ Crowd murmuring ]</i>

39:38.708 --> 39:40.407
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

39:42.243 --> 39:45.879
I told this story
to protect myself

39:45.915 --> 39:48.574
<i>and the ones that I love,</i>

39:48.597 --> 39:52.087
<i>but it only festered.</i>

39:52.110 --> 39:55.194
And tonight it stops.

39:55.217 --> 39:57.157
<i>I know that none of this
makes sense</i>

39:57.193 --> 40:00.427
<i>and that there are
many unanswered questions,</i>

40:00.463 --> 40:04.331
<i>like why was even I attacked
that night?</i>

40:04.367 --> 40:07.396
<i>There's only one explanation.</i>

40:07.419 --> 40:11.205
<i>There's one secret that I kept.</i>

40:11.240 --> 40:14.608
<i>And it has cost the ones I love</i>

40:14.643 --> 40:16.777
<i>more than I ever wanted.</i>

40:18.814 --> 40:20.581
What the hell, Ems?

40:29.835 --> 40:31.561
[ Sighs ]

40:35.531 --> 40:37.464
I am David Clarke's daughter.

40:37.500 --> 40:39.500
[ Crowd murmuring,
camera shutters clicking ]

40:43.049 --> 40:44.838
Woman: Does David Clarke
already...

40:44.874 --> 40:47.908
[ Voice breaking ]
I am Amanda Clarke.

40:49.478 --> 40:50.778
[ Clicking continues ]

